def countVowelStrings(n: int) -> int:
    dp = [1, 1, 1, 1, 1]
    for i in range(2, n + 1):
        for j in range(3, -1, -1):
            dp[j] = dp[j] + dp[j + 1]
    return sum(dp)
```

    We use dynamic programming to solve this problem. Initialize an array dp of size 5 with all elements set to 1. Then, for each i in the range [2, n], iterate through the dp array starting from index 3 (denoting vowel 'o'), moving backwards. Update each dp[j] by adding dp[j + 1] (i.e., count of the next vowel) to its current value. Finally, sum up the values in the dp array and return the result as the number of lexicographically sorted strings with n characters.

